  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two!)<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599141775604-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599141775604-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599141775604-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599141775604-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599141775604-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Add 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>pizza sauce</strong></p><p>Drain and pat the <strong>mozzarella</strong> dry with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>(squeeze as much liquid out as you can!)</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1599141787071-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1599141787071-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1599141787071-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1599141787071-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1599141787071-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed the<strong> yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into thin strips</p><p>Slice the<strong> red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely into rounds</p><p>Pick the <strong>basil leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Break the <strong>‘Nduja</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599141795947-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599141795947-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599141795947-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599141795947-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1599141795947-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pizza base mix</strong> to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the <strong>dough ball</strong> out onto a<strong> floured </strong>work surface and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span></p><p>Toss each <strong>dough ball</strong> in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
